<item>
            <title>[LU-19857] ldiskfs patch ext4-dont-check-before-replay.patch broken in 6.0+ kernels</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19857</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ext4-dont-check-before-replay.patch ldiskfs patch is broken since v6.0-rc4-47-g9c1dd22d74 due to an upstream code refactoring.  The intent of that patch was to defer group descriptor verification until after journal recovery, in case the journal replay &quot;repaired&quot; the group descriptors and would have reported an error before this (e.g. checksum or filesystem resize).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was originally added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/21141&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/21141&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8364&quot; title=&quot;during OSS failover test with quotas enabled, OSS node crashed on 2 of 4 failovers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8364&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8364&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ext4: fixes for failover mode&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
